33 auto get_math_char(uchar c, int f) -> std::string { return math_chars[c][f]; }

35 void set_math_char(uchar c, int f, std::string s) { math_chars[c][f] = std::move(s); }

39 inline void eval_let(String a, String b) { the_parser.hash_table.eval_let(a, b); }
40 void math_ns::fill_single_char() {
41  for (auto &single_char : single_chars) single_char = nullptr;
42  for (uchar x = 'a'; x <= 'z'; x++) { single_chars[x] = new Xml(the_names[np_letter_a + x - 'a']); }
43  for (uchar x = 'A'; x <= 'Z'; x++) { single_chars[x] = new Xml(the_names[np_letter_A + x - 'A']); }
44 }

1089 // Ams environments pmatrix, bmatrix, Bmatrix etc.
1090 // returns the fence values
1091 auto math_ns::special_fence(subtypes s, int &open, int &close) -> bool {
1092  switch (s) {
1093  case matrixB_code:
1094  open = del_open_brace;
1095  close = del_close_brace;
1096  break;
1097  case matrixb_code:
1098  open = del_open_bra;
1099  close = del_close_bra;
1100  break;
1101  case matrixv_code:
1102  open = del_bar;
1103  close = del_bar;
1104  break;
1105  case matrixV_code:
1106  open = del_Vert;
1107  close = del_Vert;
1108  break;
1109  case matrixp_code:
1110  open = del_open_par;
1111  close = del_close_par;
1112  break;
1113  default: return false; // no fence
1114  }
1115  return true;
1116 }

1118 // returns a delimiter position in the table
1119 // static
1120 auto math_ns::get_delimiter(CmdChr X) -> del_pos {
1121  if (X.is_other()) {
1122  if (!X.char_val().is_ascii()) return del_invalid;
1123  switch (static_cast<uchar>(X.char_val().value)) {
1124  case '<': return del_open_ket;
1125  case '>': return del_close_ket;
1126  case '.': return del_dot;
1127  case '(': return del_open_par;
1128  case ')': return del_close_par;
1129  case '[': return del_open_bra;
1130  case ']': return del_close_bra;
1131  case '|': return del_vert;
1132  case '/': return del_slash;
1133  default: return del_invalid;
1134  }
1135  }
1136  if (X.is_math_openclosebetween()) {
1137  switch (int(X.get_chr())) {
1138  case rangle_code: return del_rangle;
1139  case langle_code: return del_langle;
1140  case lbrace_code: return del_lbrace;
1141  case rbrace_code: return del_rbrace;
1142  case open_brace_code: return del_lbrace;
1143  case close_brace_code: return del_rbrace;
1144  case lceil_code: return del_lceil;
1145  case rceil_code: return del_rceil;
1146  case rfloor_code: return del_rfloor;
1147  case lfloor_code: return del_lfloor;
1148  case Vert_code: return del_Vert;
1149  case Vertx_code: return del_Vert;
1150  case vert_code: return del_vert;
1151  case lmoustache_code: return del_lmoustache;
1152  case rmoustache_code: return del_rmoustache;
1153  case uparrow_code: return del_uparrow;
1154  case downarrow_code: return del_downarrow;
1155  case updownarrow_code: return del_updownarrow;
1156  case Uparrow_code: return del_Uparrow;
1157  case Downarrow_code: return del_Downarrow;
1158  case Updownarrow_code: return del_Updownarrow;
1159  case rgroup_code: return del_rgroup;
1160  case lgroup_code: return del_lgroup;
1161  case backslash_code: return del_backslash;
1162  default:;
1163  }
1164  }
1165  if (X.is_cst1_cmd() && X.get_chr() == lbrace_chr) return del_lbrace;
1166  if (X.is_cst1_cmd() && X.get_chr() == rbrace_chr) return del_rbrace;
1167  return del_invalid;
1168 }
1169 
1170 auto math_ns::get_delimiter(int k) -> del_pos {
1171  switch (k) {
1172  case rangle_code: return del_rangle;
1173  case langle_code: return del_langle;
1174  case lbrace_code: return del_lbrace;
1175  case rbrace_code: return del_rbrace;
1176  case open_brace_code: return del_lbrace;
1177  case close_brace_code: return del_rbrace;
1178  case lceil_code: return del_lceil;
1179  case rceil_code: return del_rceil;
1180  case rfloor_code: return del_rfloor;
1181  case lfloor_code: return del_lfloor;
1182  case Vertx_code: return del_Vert;
1183  case Vert_code: return del_Vert;
1184  case vert_code: return del_vert;
1185  case lmoustache_code: return del_lmoustache;
1186  case rmoustache_code: return del_rmoustache;
1187  case uparrow_code: return del_uparrow;
1188  case downarrow_code: return del_downarrow;
1189  case updownarrow_code: return del_updownarrow;
1190  case Uparrow_code: return del_Uparrow;
1191  case Downarrow_code: return del_Downarrow;
1192  case Updownarrow_code: return del_Updownarrow;
1193  case rgroup_code: return del_rgroup;
1194  case lgroup_code: return del_lgroup;
1195  case backslash_code: return del_backslash;
1196  default:;
1197  }
1198  int n = k - math_c_loc;
1199  if (0 < n && n < 127) {
1200  switch (n) {
1201  case '<': return del_open_ket;
1202  case '>': return del_close_ket;
1203  case '.': return del_dot;
1204  case '(': return del_open_par;
1205  case ')': return del_close_par;
1206  case '[': return del_open_bra;
1207  case ']': return del_close_bra;
1208  case '|': return del_vert;
1209  case '/': return del_slash;
1210  default: return del_invalid;
1211  }
1212  }
1213  return del_invalid;
1214 }

1216 // This is a static function
1217 // true if the constant is a space.
1218 auto math_ns::math_space_code(int c) -> bool {
1219  switch (c) {
1220  case quad_code: return true;
1221  case qquad_code: return true;
1222  case space_code: return true;
1223  case exclam_code: return true;
1224  case comma_code: return true;
1225  default: return false;
1226  }
1227 }

1229 // Returns the value of a constant,
1230 auto math_ns::math_constants(int c) -> Xml * {
1231  switch (c) {
1232  case dots_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(5);
1233  case ldots_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(6);
1234  case quad_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(7);
1235  case qquad_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(8);
1236  case space_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(9);
1237  case dollar_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(10);
1238  case percent_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(11);
1239  case amp_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(12);
1240  case exclam_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(13);
1241  case comma_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(14);
1242  case lbrace_chr: return math_data.get_mc_table(15);
1243  case rbrace_chr: return math_data.get_mc_table(16);
1244  case i_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(17);
1245  case msharp_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(18);
1246  case natural_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(19);
1247  case flat_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(20);
1248  case underscore_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(21);
1249  case sharp_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(22);
1250  case j_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(23);
1251  case tdagger_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(24);
1252  case tddagger_code: return math_data.get_mc_table(25);
1253  }
1254  return math_data.get_mc_table(0);
1255 }

1257 auto MathDataP::init_builtin(String name, math_loc pos, Xml *x, symcodes t) -> Token {

1262 // This is for a general token. It defines name to be (t,pos)
1263 // It adds defined math-location pos to be <bl>ent</bl>
1264 // If hack is true, the formula $\name$ can be hacked to ent (i.e.
1265 // $\alpha$ translates to &alpha;) If no entity names are desired
1266 // then ent2 is used instead of ent, so that \alpha gives &#x3B1;
1267 
1268 auto MathDataP::mk_gen(String name, String ent, String ent2, math_loc pos, name_positions bl, symcodes t, bool hack) -> Token {
1269  Xml *x = new Xml(Istring(no_ent_names ? ent2 : ent));
1270  if (hack) built_in_table_alt[pos] = x;
1271  x = new Xml(bl, x);
1272  return init_builtin(name, pos, x, t);
1273 }
1274 
1275 // Special case where a bold variant exists
1276 auto MathDataP::mk_gen(String name, String ent, String ent2, math_loc pos, math_loc pos2, name_positions bl, symcodes t, bool hack)
1277  -> Token {
1278  Xml *x = new Xml(Istring(no_ent_names ? ent2 : ent));
1279  if (hack) built_in_table_alt[pos] = x;
1280  Xml *bold = new Xml(bl, x);
1281  bold->add_att(cst_mathvariant, cstf_bold);
1282  init_builtin(pos2, bold);
1283  x = new Xml(bl, x);
1284  return init_builtin(name, pos, x, t);
1285 }

1443 auto math_ns::make_math_char(uchar c, int n) -> Xml * {
1444  Buffer &B = the_main->SH.shbuf();
1445  B.reset();
1446  if (n <= 1)
1447  B.push_back(c);
1448  else
1449  B.push_back(math_chars[c][n]);
1450  Xml *v = new Xml(the_main->SH);
1451  Xml *res = new Xml(cst_mi, v);
1452  if (n == 1) res->add_att(cst_mathvariant, cstf_normal);
1453  return res;
1454 }

1456 void MathDataP::boot_chars() {
1457  for (int i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
1458  Istring K = the_names[cst_dig0 + i];
1459  init_builtin(i + math_dig_loc, new Xml(cst_mn, new Xml(K)));
1460  }
1461  Buffer &B = the_main->SH.shbuf();
1462 
1463  for (uchar i = 'A'; i <= 'Z'; i++) init_builtin(i + math_char_normal_loc, make_math_char(i, 0));
1464  for (uchar i = 'a'; i <= 'z'; i++) init_builtin(i + math_char_normal_loc, make_math_char(i, 0));
1465  for (uchar i = 'A'; i <= 'Z'; i++) init_builtin(i + math_char_upright_loc, make_math_char(i, 1));
1466  for (uchar i = 'a'; i <= 'z'; i++) init_builtin(i + math_char_upright_loc, make_math_char(i, 1));
1467 
1468  init_builtin(xml_e_loc, new Xml(the_names[np_letter_e]));
1469  init_builtin(xml_o_loc, new Xml(the_names[np_letter_o]));
1470  // nb_simplemath should be 128
1471  for (uchar i = 0; i < nb_simplemath; i++) {
1472  B.reset();
1473  B.push_back(i);
1474  Xml *res = new Xml(np_simplemath, new Xml(the_main->SH));
1475  Xml *X = new Xml(np_formula, res);
1476  X->add_att(np_type, np_inline);
1477  simplemath_table[i] = X;
1478  }
1479 }
